        <h2 id="Scrambled-Eggs">Scrambled Eggs</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 2 Minutes</li>
            <li>Serves: 1</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3><strong>Ingredients:</strong></h3>
        <ul>
            <li>2 Eggs</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Butter</li>
            <li>Salt and Pepper to taste</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Directions:</h3>
            
        <ol>
        <li>Heat the butter on a pan.</li>
        
        <li>Just as the butter starts browning, crack the eggs on the pan.</li>

<li>Using a spatula stir the eggs until they are no longer moist.</li>
        <li>Add salt and pepper.</li>

        </ol>
        <p><em>Source: PremAnand Rao's Recipies</em></p>
        
        <h2 id="Goli-Baje"><strong>Goli Baje (Mangalore Bonda)</strong></h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Total Time: 1 ½ hours</li>
            <li>Serves: 6</li>
        </ul>
        

        <h3><strong>Ingredients:</strong></h3>
        
                
        <ul>
                <li>½ cup Curd</li>
                <li>1 ¼ cups Water</li>
                <li>1 tsp salt</li>
                <li>1 tsp Baking Soda</li>
                <li>2 tsp Sugar</li>
                <li>2 cup Maida (All Purpose Flour)</li>
                <li>2 tbsp Besan (Chickpea Flour)</li>
                <li>4 Green Chillies</li>
        </ul>
       
       <h3>Directions:</h3>
       
       <ol>
           <li>Mix the water, curd, baking soda, and sugar together.</li>
           <li>After mixing, add besan and Maida to the batter.</li>
           <li>After mixing again, add the ginger and the green chillies. (Keep the batter aside for one hour or more).
           
           <li>Deep fry. [Note: Fry batter spoon by spoon]
           
       </ol>
       
    <p><em>Serve by itself or serve with <a href="#Coconut-Chutney">Coconut Chutney</a></em> <strong>ENJOY</strong></p>
        
    <p><em>Source: Priya Rao's Recipies</em></p>

    <h2 id="Coconut-Chutney">Coconut Chutney</h2>
    
